					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-616541#post-1831502</guid>
				<title>...it&#039;s been awhile.</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-616541/arbitrary-darkness#post-1831502</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 12 Aug 2013 23:50:08 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zyn</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1404533</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Well, since it's summer&#8230; requests are still open! No idea when I'll get around to them, but I have more time now than I did before. My only request is that if you're going to ask for a villanelle, it should be for an SCP you've written, and if possible, not rated too highly. I like using this to draw attention to less-viewed articles. ;)</p> <p>Edit: Oh, and it'd be great if those asking for requests would be willing to answer a few questions I may have during the writing process, so I don't mess up the portrayal of the SCP object.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
